{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01EXxAgBeoY7qaQvWs5EeoVt","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So `braised`, `roasted`, `white`, `herb` are in the dictionary. But `with` is NOT - it's a preposition, not a food word. So for \"Bra1sed Cod w1th Wh1te W1ne\":\n- \"Bra1sed\" → \"braised\" ✓ (dictionary match)\n- \"Cod\" → no digits, passes through\n- \"w1th\" → tries \"with\" (1→i) and \"wlth\" (1→l) - \"with\" NOT in dictionary, \"wlth\" not in dictionary → stays \"w1th\"\n\n\n- \"Wh1te\" → \"white\" ✓ (dictionary match)\n- \"W1ne\" → \"wine\" ✓ (dictionary match)\n\nAfter repair I get \"Braised Cod w1th White Wine\" - the `w1th` stays corrupted since neither candidate is in the dictionary, which would mess up the embedding scoring. For \"Roasted Beet and Walnut D1p\", the \"D1p\" would try \"dip\" and \"dlp\", but \"dip\" probably isn't in the food dictionary either since it's more of a general cooking term.\n\nThe real problem is that common English words like \"with\", \"the\", and \"and\" aren't in the food ingredient dictionary, so OCR repair fails on them. I need to either add these common words to the dictionary or use a different repair strategy altogether. Let me check the code flow - looking at `buildCandidates`, I can see that `repairOcrText` is actually called before the hard filters, so the repair is happening, but incomplete repairs are leaving artifacts that hurt embedding quality. I should outline what needs to change here.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3057,"cache_read_input_tokens":81257,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":3057},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d80e2ded-f7a7-46bb-8be0-f1bcb73047ba","uuid":"84bd0c96-1573-464d-ac78-3d69283a185b"}
